{{italic title}} {{About|the encyclical issued by Pope Gregory XVI|other uses|Cum Primum (disambiguation){{!}}Cum primum}}
'''''Cum primum''''', subtitled ''On Civil Disobedience'', is an [[encyclical]] issued by [[Pope Gregory XVI]] on June 9, 1832.<ref name="full text">{{cite web|title=Cum primum|publisher=Papal Encyclicals Online|url=http://www.papalencyclicals.net/Greg16/g16cumpr.htm|accessdate=July 9, 2014}}</ref>
The encyclical is addressed to the [[Bishop|episcopate]] of the [[Congress Poland|Kingdom of Poland]] and is primarily a condemnation of the [[November Uprising]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Hittinger |first=F. Russell |author-link=Russell Hittinger |title=The Teachings of Modern Christianity on Law, Politics, and Human Nature: Volume One |publisher=Columbia University Press |date= |pages=8–9|chapter=Chapter 1: Introduction to Modern Catholicism |isbn= }}</ref>
