{{Infobox UN resolution |number = 77 |organ = SC |date = October 11 |year = 1949 |meeting = 450 |code = S/1403 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/77(1949) |for = 9 |abstention = 2 |against = 0 |subject = Armaments: regulation and reduction |result = Adopted |image = |caption = }}
'''[[United Nations]] [[United Nations Security Council Resolution|Security Council Resolution]] 77''', adopted on 11 October 1949, having received and examined the second progress report of the [[United Nations Commission on Conventional Armaments|Commission for Conventional Armaments]], the Council directed the [[United Nations Secretary-General|Secretary-General]] to transmit the report, along with its annexes, accompanying resolution and a record of the [[UNSC|Council]]’s consideration of the subject to the [[United Nations General Assembly|General Assembly]] for its information.
The resolution was adopted with nine votes in favour and two abstentions from the [[Ukrainian SSR]] and [[Soviet Union]].
